            text: ' yet, but it is starting to move away from being a plain collision lab. There are platforms, pickups, lock-box ideas, and enough route shape to expose problems. That is useful. A rough level that reveals bad assumptions is far more valuable than a pretty screen that does nothing.',
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        type: 'pullquote',
        text: 'A rough level that reveals bad assumptions is far more valuable than a pretty screen that does nothing.',
