      },
      {
        type: 'paragraph',
        content: [
          {
            text: 'Monday morning started with a small goal: add collision detection, even if it only reported results to the Console. That is not exciting in the marketing sense, but it is exactly the kind of work the game needs right now. Before score, packages, locks, buttons, and meanies can matter, the game needs to reliably know when the player touched something.',
          },
